	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001313_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Cape Town</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">30 April </p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir </p>
<lb/><p>The account 
<lb/>you have presented 
<lb/>to me is clearly 
<lb/>for an appeal 
<lb/>made by you 
<lb/>in behalf of the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001313_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'-->
<lb/>funds of the Society 
<lb/>in order that 
<lb/>advantage might 
<lb/>be taken of my 
<lb/>discoveries and 
<lb/>new missions 
<lb/>established. It 
<lb/>was intended also 
<lb/>to defray my 
<lb/>expenses, but 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001313_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/>mainly to increase 
<lb/>the Society's funds, 
<lb/>but the appeal 
<lb/>was abortive, 
<lb/>and the expenses 
<lb/>ought to be borne 
<lb/>by the Society. </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am Dear Sir </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Yours Truly </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>Rev<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">d</hi></hi> W<hi rend="sup underline">m</hi> Thompson</persName></p>
			
</div>
